Setting the Dose Rate Alarm

View the Setpoint

  • Press and hold the ALARM button and then press the RATE button.
  • Release both buttons, and the display will flash the set point value for the Rate Alarm.
  • The unit will return to displaying the Rate in about 10 seconds if no further actions are performed.

Changing the Dose Rate Alarm Set Point

  • While in RATE mode, press and hold the ALARM button and then press the RATE button.
  • Release both buttons and the display will flash the set point value for the RATE ALARM.
  • Within 10 seconds, press and release the CLR/TEST button.

Change the Rate Alarm

  • Repeatedly press and release the RATE button until the desired units of measurement (µGy/hr, cGy/hr, or Gy/hr) and decimal point location are displayed. Set the RATE based on unit SOP. Note: You can change the units of measurement as well as by cycling through the different units.
  • Next, press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock the selected Decimal Point location. The left-most digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the RATE button until the desired left-most digit is displayed.
  • Now, press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock in the left-most digit. The center digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the RATE button until the desired center digit is displayed.
  • Press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock in the center digit. The right-most digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the RATE button until the desired right-most digit is displayed.
  • To lock in the right-most digit, press and release the CLR/TEST button.
  • Once this process has been completed, the Radiacmeter will display the RATE ALARM setting for approximately 10 seconds and then return to the RATE mode.
